'''Achziv Islands''' (also '''Achziv Beach Islands''') are a group of small [[Israel]] [[Island|islands]] in the [[Mediterranean Sea]]. Each island is a few hundred square meters in area, with a  reef is composed of  small [[limestone]] blocks. 

The Achziv islands - Nahlieli, Shahaf and Achziv -  are located west of the Akhziv shore. They are actually the tops of a sunken sandstone ridge. Seagulls and terns nest on Nahlieli. The islands are part of the [[Rosh Hanikra Islands]] Nature Reserve.<ref>[http://www.parks.org.il/sites/English/ParksAndReserves/achziv/Pages/default.aspx Observation points, Akhziv National Park]</ref> 
