[[Image:Britanski trg Zagreb.jpg|thumb|right|Britanski trg]]
'''Britanski trg''' ('''British Square''') is a [[public square]] in the city of [[Zagreb]], [[Croatia]].<ref>{{cite web |author=Shaun Madison |url=http://www.mbendi.com/a_sndmsg/place_view.asp?pid=4253505 |title=Britanski trg, Croatia |publisher=Mbendi.com |date= |accessdate=2010-02-25 }}{{Dead link|date=November 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> It is one of the few remaining squares to include an open-air [[farmers' market]]place with fresh fruit, vegetables and other foods brought directly from farms,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vegguide.org/entry/7457 |title=Britanski Trg Market |publisher=VegGuide.Org |date= |accessdate=2010-02-25}}</ref> and is a revered urban area among the population of Zagreb.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hart.hr/projekti/istrazivanja/54/britanski-trg-nastanak-i-urbani-status |title=Britanski trg: nastanak i urbani status |publisher=Hart.hr |date=2004-02-13 |accessdate=2010-02-25 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721100155/http://www.hart.hr/projekti/istrazivanja/54/britanski-trg-nastanak-i-urbani-status |archivedate=July 21, 2011 }}</ref> Britanski trg is located along [[Ilica (street)|Ilica Street]], a few blocks west from the main city square, [[Ban Jelačić Square]]. It is also a [[transport hub]]—it is an endpoint for several bus lines, while the [[Zagreb tram system|city tram]] lines 1, 6 and 11 stop on its south side.<ref>{{cite web|title=Regular Tram Services|url=http://www.zet.hr/UserDocsImages/Prilozi/PDF/dnevna%20tram%20mre%C5%BEa.pdf|publisher=[[Zagrebački električni tramvaj]]|accessdate=23 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150428234847/http://www.zet.hr/UserDocsImages/Prilozi/PDF/dnevna%20tram%20mre%C5%BEa.pdf#|archive-date=2015-04-28|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref> The square itself is convenient for access to several elite upscale neighborhoods of Zagreb, such as [[Pantovčak]] and [[Zelengaj]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.karte.hr/lokacije/britanski-trg |title=Britanski trg |publisher=karte.hr |date= |accessdate=2010-02-25}}</ref> The open air market is held daily from early morning until about noon, and an antiques fair is held at the square each Sunday.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.absolute-croatia.com/shop/zagreb/britanski_trg |title=Britanski Trg (British Square) &#124; Absolute World - Croatia |publisher=Absolute-croatia.com |date= |accessdate=2010-02-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091123030315/http://www.absolute-croatia.com/shop/zagreb/britanski_trg# |archive-date=2009-11-23 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.inyourpocket.com/croatia/zagreb/shopping/markets/farmers-market-britanski-trg-3749v |title=Markets Farmer's Market - Britanski trg - Shopping in Zagreb - In Your Pocket city guide - essential travel guides to cities in Croatia |publisher=Inyourpocket.com |date= |accessdate=2010-02-25 }}{{Dead link|date=November 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

