{{Infobox feature on celestial object |name = Hayabusa Terra |image = |caption = |type = [[Planetary nomenclature#terra|terra]] |location = [[Pluto]] |coordinates= {{coord|53|N|120|W|globe:pluto_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} |coordinates_footnotes = |length = |width = |diameter = |depth = |area = |dimensions = |peak = |discoverer = ''[[New Horizons]]'' |naming = ''[[Hayabusa]]'' |eponym = }}
'''Hayabusa Terra''' {{IPAc-en|,|h|ai|@|'|b|u:|s|@}} is a surface feature on the [[dwarf planet]] [[Pluto]]. It was discovered by the ''[[New Horizons]]'' spacecraft in July 2015. It is named for ''[[Hayabusa]]'', the first spacecraft to successfully [[Sample return|return a sample]] of an [[asteroid]] to Earth. The name has been officially approved by the [[International Astronomical Union]] on 7 September 2017.<ref name = "name approval">{{cite web|url=https://www.nasa.gov/feature/pluto-features-given-first-official-names|title=Pluto Features Given First Official Names|publisher=[[NASA]]|date=7 September 2017}}</ref>
