''[[Frozen (2013 film)|Frozen]]'' is a 2013 American [[3D film|3D]] [[Computer animation|computer-animated]] film produced by [[Walt Disney Animation Studios]] and released by [[Walt Disney Pictures]]. It was directed by [[Chris Buck]] and [[Jennifer Lee (filmmaker)|Jennifer Lee]], the latter of whom also wrote the screenplay, and was produced by [[Peter Del Vecho]]. The film focuses on [[Anna (Disney)|Anna]], a princess who sets off on a journey to find her estranged sister, [[Elsa (Disney)|Elsa]], whose icy powers have inadvertently trapped their kingdom in eternal winter.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/film/frozen/review/ |title=Frozen is squeezably lovely |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |date=April 15, 2015 |last=Collin |first=Robbie |accessdate=September 27, 2016 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160815094319/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/film/frozen/review/ |archivedate=August 15, 2016 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://variety.com/2013/film/reviews/frozen-review-1200782020/ |title=Film Review: 'Frozen' |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=November 3, 2013 |accessdate=September 27, 2016 |last=Foundas |first=Scott |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160517190554/http://variety.com/2013/film/reviews/frozen-review-1200782020/ |archivedate=May 17, 2016 |df= }}</ref>

The film premiered at the [[El Capitan Theatre]] in [[Hollywood]], [[California]], on November 19, 2013, before going into wide release on November 27 in over 3,700 theatres in the United States and Canada. It debuted in second place, earning more than $67 million. The film grossed a worldwide total of over $1.27 billion on a production budget of $150 million.<ref name="Box Office Mojo">{{cite web|url=http://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=frozen2013.htm |title=Frozen |publisher=[[Box Office Mojo]] |accessdate=September 27, 2016 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161001133044/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=frozen2013.htm |archivedate=October 1, 2016 |df= }}</ref> {{As of|2016|09}}, ''Frozen'' is the [[List of highest-grossing animated films|highest-grossing animated film of all time]], and was the [[2013 in film|highest-grossing film of 2013]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-26815584 |title=Frozen becomes the biggest animation in box office history |publisher=[[BBC News]] |accessdate=March 13, 2015 |date=March 31, 2014 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150220033351/http://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-26815584 |archivedate=February 20, 2015 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=2013 Worldwide Grosses |url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/yearly/chart/?view2=worldwide&yr=2013 |publisher=[[Box Office Mojo]] |accessdate=August 26, 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305215244/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/yearly/chart/?view2=worldwide&yr=2013 |archivedate=March 5, 2016 |df= }}</ref> [[Rotten Tomatoes]], a [[review aggregator]], surveyed 227 reviews, and judged 89 percent to be positive.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/frozen_2013/ |title=Frozen (2013) |publisher=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |accessdate=November 22, 2017|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161109021457/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/frozen_2013 |archivedate=November 9, 2016 |df= }}</ref>

''Frozen'' garnered a variety of awards and nominations, many of them in the Best Original Song (for "[[Let It Go (Disney song)|Let It Go]]") and Best Animated Feature categories. At the [[71st Golden Globe Awards]], the film earned two nominations, winning for [[Golden Globe Award for Best Animated Feature Film|Best Animated Feature Film]].<ref name=GGnom/><ref name=GGwin/> At the [[41st Annie Awards]], ''Frozen'' joint-led the nominations with ''[[Monsters University]]'', both earning ten nominations.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2013/film/awards/annie-awards-nominations-1200909634/ |title='Frozen,' 'Monsters University' Top Annie Awards Noms with 10 Each |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=December 2, 2013 |accessdate=July 15, 2014 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140217120139/http://variety.com/2013/film/awards/annie-awards-nominations-1200909634/ |archivedate=February 17, 2014 |df= }}</ref> The film went on to win five [[Annie Award]]s, including [[Annie Award for Best Animated Feature|Best Animated Feature]].<ref name=Anniewin/> At the [[86th Academy Awards]], ''Frozen'' became the first film by Walt Disney Animation Studios to win the [[Academy Award for Best Animated Feature]],<ref>{{cite web|last1=Richwine |first1=Lisa |last2=Grover |first2=Ron |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2014/03/03/us-oscars-animation-idUSBREA1R0MN20140303 |title=Disney's 'Frozen' wins animated feature Oscar |work=[[Reuters]] |date=March 2, 2014 |accessdate=July 15, 2014 |location=Los Angeles |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140505073253/https://www.reuters.com/article/2014/03/03/us-oscars-animation-idUSBREA1R0MN20140303 |archivedate=May 5, 2014 |df= }}</ref> and won the [[Academy Award for Best Original Song|Best Original Song]] award for "Let It Go".<ref name=Oscarwin/> ''Frozen'' also won the [[BAFTA Award for Best Animated Film]] and the [[Critics' Choice Movie Award]] for both [[Critics' Choice Movie Award for Best Animated Feature|Best Animated Feature]] and [[Critics' Choice Movie Award for Best Song|Best Song]].<ref name=BAFTAwin/><ref name=Criticswin/> At the [[57th Annual Grammy Awards]], the [[Frozen (soundtrack)|''Frozen'' soundtrack]] won the award for [[Grammy Award for Best Compilation Soundtrack for Visual Media|Best Compilation Soundtrack for Visual Media]] and "Let It Go" won the award for [[Grammy Award for Best Song Written for Visual Media|Best Song Written for Visual Media]].<ref name="ABC Grammys">{{cite web|last1=Fekadu|first1=Mesfin|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/wireStory/show-bits-frozen-soundtrack-fires-grammy-wins-28817993|title=Show Bits: : 'Frozen' Soundtrack Fires up With 2 Grammy Wins|publisher=[[ABC News]]|location=Los Angeles|accessdate=February 9, 2015|date=February 8, 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150209035036/http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/wireStory/show-bits-frozen-soundtrack-fires-grammy-wins-28817993|archivedate=February 9, 2015}}</ref> The film's visual effects were acclaimed by the [[Visual Effects Society]], which gave the film awards in all four of its animated film categories.<ref name=VSwin/>

