{{Use Australian English|date=November 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=November 2014}} {{Infobox waterfall | name = Nigretta Falls | photo = 20090927_Nigretta_Falls_-_Victoria_-_Australia.JPG | photo_width = 270px | photo_caption = Nigretta Falls | map = Australia Victoria | map_width = 270 | map_caption = Location of the Nigretta Falls in [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]] | relief = yes | coords = {{coord|37|39|22|S|141|55|28|E|region:AU-VIC_type:waterbody_source:kolossus-eswiki|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = | location = [[Grampians (region) |Grampian]], [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]], [[Australia]] | type = Segmented | elevation = | height = | height_longest = | number_drops = ''numerous'' | width = | average_width = | watercourse = [[Wannon River]] | average_flow = | world_rank = }} The '''Nigretta Falls''',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.world-of-waterfalls.com/australia-nigretta-falls.html|title=Nigretta Falls|work=World of Waterfalls|author=Cheng, Johnny T.|date=|accessdate=17 November 2014}}</ref> previously known as the '''Upper Wannon Falls''',<ref>{{Cite VICNAMES|122583|Nigretta Falls|accessdate=17 November 2014}}</ref> are [[waterfall]]s located in the [[Shire of Southern Grampians|Southern Grampians Shire]], approximately {{convert|16|km}} west of [[Hamilton, Victoria|Hamilton]], [[Victoria, Australia|Victoria]], [[Australia]]. The falls are fed by the [[Wannon River]] that has its head waters in the [[Grampians National Park|Grampians mountains]].
==Location and features== The falls tumble over many rocky outcrops creating several streams of falling water and then drop into a large pool at the base before continuing its journey to the [[Wannon Falls]] some {{convert|10|km}} downstream. In contrast to the single plunge of the [[Wannon Falls]], Nigretta is a more interesting, multi-channel segmented cascade of smaller drops and bounces guided by patterns of joints in a much older (Devonian) [[rhyolitic]] volcanic rock.<ref>{{cite web|last=Grimes|first=Ken|title=Wannon & Nigretta Falls|url=http://hamilton-field-naturalists-club-victoria.org.au/images/pdf/D/wannon%20%20nigretta%20falls%20kg2005.pdf|accessdate=19 September 2012}}</ref> However, as with the Wannon Falls, the amount of water varies with the time of year - the photo shows a late winter, wet season, view. The Nigretta Scenic Reserve includes parts of the Wannon River Valley which contains representatives of the native plants of the Dundas Tablelands, listed in the reference.<ref>{{cite web|last=Bird|first=Rod|title=HFNC weed control work at Nigretta Falls Scenic Reserve|url=http://hamilton-field-naturalists-club-victoria.org.au/images/pdf/M/weedcontrolnigrettascenicresnov2011.pdf|accessdate=19 September 2012}}</ref>
==See also== {{Stack|{{portal|Victoria|Environment}}}} *[[List of waterfalls of Australia#Victoria|List of waterfalls of Victoria]]
